# Int2 overflow tests

(tx 'create schema test')
(tx 'create table test.item(field: int2)')
!tx 'insert (32768) into test.item (field)'
---
> error[PO0001]: value overflows column `field` type `INT2`
>   1 │ insert (32768) into test.item (field)
>     │         ^
>     = value `32768` does not fit into `INT2` (range: -32,768 to 32,767)
> 
> note: column `field` is of type `INT2`
> 
> help: reduce the value, change the column type to a wider type or change the overflow policy
